title: South Korea 2 Year Note Yield
description: South Korea 2 Year Bond Yield was 4.25 percent on Tuesday November 8, according to over-the-counter interbank yield quotes for this government bond maturity. Historically, the South Korea 2 Year Note Yield reached an all time high of 6.40 in April of 2010. This page includes a chart with historical data for South Korea 2Y.
